  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The infrapyloric (No.206) and greater curvature (No.204) lymph node metastasis in&#xD;
      adenocarcinoma located at hepatic flexure and right half of transverse colon has not been&#xD;
      well discribed and analysed. The aim of this study is to assess the rate of this lymph node&#xD;
      metastasis and to reveal its prognostic value for colon cancer located at hepatic flexure and&#xD;
      right half of transverse colon. Meanwhile, we can evaluate the safety and feasibility of this&#xD;
      extented lymphadenectomy in right hemi-colectomy.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
